responses.title: The threads of fate are mine to weave.
The loom weaves and a new pattern appears.
More fates for me to weave.
The threads of fate are mine to weave.
The loom weaves and a new pattern appears.
Caught in your own life's thread.
You thought you had me, didn't you?
Ah, I see more of the pattern.
I'll thread the needle through your eyes.
Shuttle and loom, I weave your doom.
To the loom with you, to be rewoven.
Who puts their skeleton on the inside?
That's no way to protect your vitals.
What sort of bug are you, Assassin?
It's all part of the pattern.
I've been weaving my way toward this.
I'll cut their threads with this dagger.
Weave your spell on me, scepter.
Our fates were woven from the first.
I hate to leave loose ends.
I'll weave a brighter pattern this time.
More fates for me to weave.
The Loom weaves my life anew.
I must repair what came undone.
My life by the Loom rewoven.
There's a snag in your plans.
You'll have a place in the pattern.
Few know their place in the cosmic weave. Fewer still can lay their claws upon the Loom and influence the pattern.
Fate weaves the threads of our lives together. Fate also wields the blade that cuts them short.
